140
00:12:14,165 --> 00:12:17,330
I didn't want you to give up on yourself.

141
00:12:19,759 --> 00:12:22,330
Light is always➡

142
00:12:22,330 --> 00:12:25,363
It feels like I'm going my own way.

143
00:12:25,363 --> 00:12:27,858
Hehe...

144
00:12:27,858 --> 00:12:32,363
Well, I've had a lot of troubles too.

145
00:12:32,363 --> 00:12:35,363
Look, it was my second year at university➡

146
00:12:35,363 --> 00:12:39,099
The first time I told a club that I was gay➡

147
00:12:39,099 --> 00:12:41,165
There were quite a few people who said a lot of things to me.

148
00:12:41,165 --> 00:12:45,099
Yes, it was there.

149
00:12:45,099 --> 00:12:48,825
But then, Chinami said.

150
00:12:48,825 --> 00:12:52,363
The me I was before I said "I'm gay" and the me I was after I said it ➡

151
00:12:52,363 --> 00:12:54,462
Nothing will change.

152
00:12:54,462 --> 00:12:57,495
Did you say that? I said it.

153
00:12:57,495 --> 00:12:59,957
So…➡

154
00:12:59,957 --> 00:13:02,396
``Well, just because I'm a man➡

155
00:13:02,396 --> 00:13:04,693
Do you think you will be chosen by the light? ➡

156
00:13:04,693 --> 00:13:07,297
Congratulations.” Hehe…hehehe.

157
00:13:07,297 --> 00:13:09,693
what? that. I? Yeah.

158
00:13:09,693 --> 00:13:12,429
Stop it!

159
00:13:12,429 --> 00:13:17,330
I feel like I was completely blown away by those words.

160
00:13:19,693 --> 00:13:22,165
That's right.

161
00:13:22,165 --> 00:13:26,297
So I also do a lot of things on land...

162
00:13:29,297 --> 00:13:32,231
Riku-kun...➡

163
00:13:32,231 --> 00:13:34,594
I guess that was hard...

164
00:13:36,297 --> 00:13:38,330
Huh?

165
00:13:38,330 --> 00:13:43,726
I understand that Hikari wishes for Riku-kun's happiness.

166
00:13:43,726 --> 00:13:49,693
It's about someone you like. I can understand supporting them.

167
00:13:49,693 --> 00:13:52,066
But…➡

168
00:13:52,066 --> 00:13:56,660
Riku-kun is the one who decides his happiness.

169
00:13:58,099 --> 00:14:00,495
I know that.

170
00:14:00,495 --> 00:14:05,429
Yes, that's right.

171
00:14:05,429 --> 00:14:09,726
You know the light, right? Hehe...

172
00:14:09,726 --> 00:14:14,858
But I can understand something.

173
00:14:14,858 --> 00:14:19,165
How does your lover see you?

174
00:14:19,165 --> 00:14:23,693
♬〜

175
00:14:23,693 --> 00:14:28,495
Riku-kun...only for the light➡

176
00:14:28,495 --> 00:14:33,330
I guess he didn't want people to think he was giving up.

177
00:14:33,330 --> 00:14:51,000
♬〜

178
00:14:53,660 --> 00:14:56,231
yes. thank you.

179
00:14:58,330 --> 00:15:00,528
Good...

180
00:15:00,528 --> 00:15:05,033
You can say all you want about other people➡

181
00:15:05,033 --> 00:15:08,330
When it comes to myself, I really...

182
00:15:08,330 --> 00:15:11,000
Hey. Hehe... Hey.

183
00:15:15,957 --> 00:15:18,000
delicious.

184
00:15:19,627 --> 00:15:21,660
Something happened to Chinami too, right?

185
00:15:25,198 --> 00:15:29,165
Hmm….

186
00:15:29,165 --> 00:15:31,495
Well, I'm Chinami➡

187
00:15:31,495 --> 00:15:34,099
Even though I said I was going to marry a 30-year-old grandpa.

188
00:15:34,099 --> 00:15:36,891
Hehe what? that.

189
00:15:36,891 --> 00:15:40,066
She said she would become the third wife of an Arab oil tycoon.

190
00:15:40,066 --> 00:15:42,231
It's the best.

191
00:15:42,231 --> 00:15:46,264
No matter what happens, I'll be on Chinami's side.

192
00:15:52,198 --> 00:15:54,231
Yeah.

193
00:15:58,330 --> 00:16:07,561
♬〜

194
00:16:07,561 --> 00:16:11,330
(Senpai) Then I'll ask you to let me off. (Riku) Yes! ➡

195
00:16:11,330 --> 00:16:13,363
Good.

196
00:16:13,363 --> 00:16:33,000
♬〜

197
00:16:33,000 --> 00:16:49,000
♬〜

198
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:51,033
(Murata) Gohogoho….

199
00:16:51,033 --> 00:16:55,561
♬〜

200
00:16:55,561 --> 00:16:57,594
(Murata/Ayo) Thank you for your hard work.

201
00:16:59,825 --> 00:17:01,858
Murata.

202
00:17:01,858 --> 00:17:16,627
♬〜

203
00:17:16,627 --> 00:17:18,660
give.

204
00:17:18,660 --> 00:17:33,495
♬〜

205
00:17:33,495 --> 00:17:35,528
(Murata) That's sweet...

206
00:17:50,594 --> 00:17:53,759
(Shibuya) I'll get to the hotel early, so let's relax in the room.

207
00:17:55,528 --> 00:17:57,561
Yeah.

208
00:18:28,660 --> 00:18:37,099
♬〜

209
00:18:37,099 --> 00:18:39,924
(Shibuya) So beautiful.

210
00:18:39,924 --> 00:18:43,924
You can see the ocean from the open air of your room. ➡

211
00:18:43,924 --> 00:18:45,957
So, drink beer while watching the sunset...

212
00:18:45,957 --> 00:18:49,099
Get off. (Shibuya) Huh?

213
00:18:49,099 --> 00:18:51,132
Get off! (Shibuya) Huh? ➡

214
00:18:51,132 --> 00:18:54,000
Hey... wait a minute! I'll stop now.

215
00:19:08,957 --> 00:19:10,990
sorry.

216
00:19:12,429 --> 00:19:14,759
I can't go after all.

217
00:19:14,759 --> 00:19:17,495
(Shibuya) Huh…. why?

218
00:19:17,495 --> 00:19:19,528
Why all of a sudden?

219
00:19:23,330 --> 00:19:25,363
I….

220
00:19:27,660 --> 00:19:30,396
Something was wrong.

221
00:19:30,396 --> 00:19:40,660
♬〜

222
00:19:40,660 --> 00:19:46,099
About Shibuya-san... I liked him.

223
00:19:49,462 --> 00:19:51,561
But that's...

224
00:19:54,924 --> 00:19:56,990
So kind...

225
00:19:59,594 --> 00:20:01,627
It's sweet...

226
00:20:04,462 --> 00:20:08,726
For me too➡

227
00:20:08,726 --> 00:20:11,165
I think it was because it was convenient.

228
00:20:12,924 --> 00:20:14,957
Chinami...

229
00:20:14,957 --> 00:20:19,528
♬〜

230
00:20:19,528 --> 00:20:21,561
Bang (car door sound)

231
00:20:21,561 --> 00:20:36,066
♬〜

232
00:20:38,660 --> 00:20:40,693
good bye.

233
00:21:04,132 --> 00:21:06,165
It was refreshing!

234
00:21:06,165 --> 00:21:16,495
♬〜

235
00:21:16,495 --> 00:21:19,066
How should I go home?

236
00:21:19,066 --> 00:21:38,726
♬〜

237
00:21:38,726 --> 00:21:42,132
(Voice of the heart) ≪We are in love≫

238
00:21:45,297 --> 00:21:48,660
≪Meet and be attracted to each other≫

239
00:21:48,660 --> 00:21:50,825
Ahead. (Ariga) Good work.

240
00:21:52,891 --> 00:21:56,924
≪Tied and hurt≫

241
00:22:00,957 --> 00:22:02,990
≪It's a mess≫

242
00:22:02,990 --> 00:22:09,693
